## Testing
{% if has_python %}
```bash
# Run all tests
./scripts/test.sh

# Run specific file
./scripts/test.sh tests/unit/test_example.py

# Run specific class
./scripts/test.sh tests/unit/test_example.py::TestClass

# Run specific test
./scripts/test.sh tests/unit/test_example.py::TestClass::test_method

# Pattern matching
./scripts/test.sh -k "test_config"

# Re-run failed tests
./scripts/test.sh --failed

# Skip coverage
./scripts/test.sh --no-cov

# Pass args to pytest
./scripts/test.sh -- -x --pdb
```
